# URL Parameters ğŸ†”

Capture values from the URL.

Route: `<Route path="/users/:id" element={<User />} />`

Inside component, use `useParams()` hook:

```jsx
import { useParams } from 'react-router-dom';
function User() {
  let { id } = useParams();
  return <h1>User ID: {id}</h1>;
}
```

# useNavigate ğŸ§­

Navigate using code (e.g., after form submission).

```jsx
import { useNavigate } from 'react-router-dom';

function Login() {
  const navigate = useNavigate();

  const handleSubmit = () => {
    // ... login logic
    navigate('/dashboard');
  };
}
```

# Protected Routes ğŸ›¡ï¸

Prevent access if not logged in.

Create a wrapper component:
```jsx
function RequireAuth({ children }) {
  const auth = useAuth();
  if (!auth.user) {
    return <Navigate to="/login" />;
  }
  return children;
}
```

